      "text": [
        " «تُتِمُّ سَعْيَهَا » وَ سَأَلَهُ عَنِ اِمْرَأَةٍ طَافَتْ بِالْبَيْتِ ثُمَّ حَاضَتْ قَبْلَ أَنْ تَسْعَى قَالَ «تَسْعَى."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.bab-ul-qaim-publications": [
          "Hadith.2757 - Mu'awiyah ibn Ammar asked Abu Abdullah (as) about a woman who began her sa‘i between Safa and Marwa but started menstruating before completing it.\nImam (as) said: \"She should complete her sa‘i.\"\nHe also asked about a woman who performed tawaf around the Kaaba and then menstruated before performing sa‘i.\nImam (as) said: \"She should perform sa‘i.\""
        ]
      }
    },
